quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  6,9,"And had We appointed an angel, We would have had to send him in the form of a man too (that he may speak to men) and this would have made perplexing for them that which they deem perplexing now"
  6,10,"There have been Messengers before you who were mocked at, but that at which they mocked surrounded (mocked, turned the tables on) the mockers"
  6,11,"Say, \"Travel in the land and see the nature of the consequences for the rejecters (for those who called them liars)"
  6,12,"Say, \"Whose is that which is in the heavens and the earth?\" Say, \"AllahÂ´s. He has imposed (prescribed) mercy on himself.\" He will surely gather you together on the Day (of Resurrection and Judgment), of which there is no doubt. B"
  6,13,"His is whatsoever dwells in the night or in the day, He is Hearer and Knower"
  6,14,"Say, \"Shall I take as a patron other than Allah, the Originator of the heavens and the earth? He feeds but is not fed.\" Say, \"I am bidden to be the first of those who Surrender;\" and it was said to me, \"Be not you of the idolaters"
  6,15,"Say, \"I fear, if I rebel against my Lord, the retribution of an Awful Day"
  6,16,"From whomsoever it is averted on that day, Allah hath truly had mercy on him; and that is obvious triumph (salvation, success, happiness, fulfilment)"
  6,17,"And if Allah touch you with harm (affliction, ill fortune), there is none can remove it but He; and if He touch you with good, He has Power over all things"
  6,18,"He is Omnipotent (sovereign) over His servants, He is the Wise, the Aware"